title: Neutron beam facility at the Louvain-la-Neuve isochronous cyclotron; cross sections for fast neutron production.

isochronous cyclotron; cross sections for fast neutron

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Instrum.and Methods in Physics Res., Vol.148, p.363 (1978)

x4freetext: Neutrons are detected by an NE213 liquid
scintillator coupled to an XP 2020 photomultiplier. The
cylindrical liquid dimensions are 19 mm diameter and
The gas cell is a stainless steel container of 8 mm
wall thickness, 15 cm high and 14 cm diameter. The
primary beam windows are in Havar metal of 12.mu-m
Solid targets have a 20 mm diameter and are cooled, by
REACTION code in Sub 002-014 was changed.
